condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I.A | Description :Maintain the Project Coordination Committee and Project Management Unit;carry out the Project in accordance with the Project Operational Manual. | Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I.B | Description :Project is carried out in accordance with the provisions of theAnti-Corruption Guidelines. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I.C | Description :Carry out the Project in accordance with the Environmental AssessmentManagement Framework and the Land Acquisition and Resettlement Policy Framework. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I.D | Description :Select, appraise, implement and evaluate Sub-projects in accordance withthe POM and provide Sub-loans or Grants to selected Participating Municipalities on terms and conditions satisfactory to the Bank.|Frequency :Yearly

title.narrative: Percentage of participating municipalities that regularly publish benchmarks & sub-project progress information on their municipal or CSE's websites, and on PMU's Project portal
Percentage of planned beneficiary feedback/citizen engagement activities implemented
Length of improved local road infrastructure as a result of constructed or reconstructed local roads structure under the Project
Number of people benetited from improved local road infrastructure under the Project
Number of municipalities receiving a performance investment grant

Nb of particip.municip. implementing institutional dvpt reforms contributing to PDO, as evidenced by nb of municip. that meet 4 or more of the 7 perform. criteria (ie that qualify for perform. grants)
Number of applications to access funds (performance investment grant) under Component C
Number of municipalities that qualify for sub-loans (ie meet the eligibility criteria to participate in MSIP)
Number of participating CSEs and/or municipalities supported by TA activities under Component B
Improved financial performance as reflected by the percentage of participating municipalities achieving increased revenue earnings and/or cost savings in completed sub-project.
Percentage of participating municipalities achieving targeted improvements in delivery of selected services in completed sub-projects
Satisfactory completion of TA contracts with outputs accepted by the clients

target.value: Satisfactory completion of TA contracts supported by the project with outputs accepted by the clients

actual.value: The following TA have been satisfactorily completed, including: TA to analyse technological options and O&M arrangements related towastewater treatment in the rural areas, TA to analyze block grants to municipalities. TA for preparation of technical designs forstreets and local roads for the N. Macedonian municipalities is underway with technical designs for 10 municipalities alreadydelivered. Furthermore, portion of TA funds is used to finance Energy Efficiency specialist to help to develop pipeline ofinvestments for the forthcoming Energy Efficiency Project (planned to be financed by the World Bank).

title.narrative: Continued and sustained dialogue on institutional reform as evidenced by submission of studies, such as a Strategy for Financial Intermediation for Municipal Investments

target.value: Studies to inform and contribute to potential municipal finance and municipal services reforms are undertaken and submitted to theMinistry of Finance

actual.value: 2 input studies completed. Approach on the next steps is being discussed with the government, including recommendations from the WBfunded municipal finance ASA that was officially communicated to the government in October 2019

title.narrative: Number of people in urban areas provided with access to regular solid waste collection under the project
Piped household water connections that are benefiting from rehabilitation works undertaken by the project
Number of sub-projects successfully completed under Component E
Number of municipalities receiving a grant from IPA window under Component E
